  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Trade Operations Executive (Dry Bulk)",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Execute end-to-end sugar shipments (container or bulk).</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with shipping lines, freight forwarders, surveyors, and warehouses.</p></li><li><p>Prepare and handle shipping documents: B/L, invoices, COO, certificates, LC documentation.</p></li><li><p>Ensure contract terms, Incoterms, and GAFTA/FOSFA requirements are met.</p></li><li><p>Track shipment status, resolve operational issues, and manage updates to traders.</p></li><li><p>Support demurrage calculations, claims, and compliance.</p></li><li><p>Work with finance on invoices, payments, LC processing, and cost reconciliation.</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Diploma/Degree in Business, Supply Chain, Logistics, or related fields.</p></li><li><p>2–5 years of commodity or shipping operations experience (soft commodities preferred).</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of LC documents, shipping procedures, and Incoterms.</p></li><li><p>Strong coordination, communication, and problem-solving skills.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Excel; experience with trading/ERP systems is a plus.</p></li></ul>",
